    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Edward M. House Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">E. M. House</persName> to the
                        British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lloyd George</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Green Wood Gate, Ashdown Forrest</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Withyham, Sussex</hi>
                        </placeName>.<date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-12">August 12,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Prime Minister</hi>: Thank you so much for wanting me
                    to lunch yesterday with Grey and Haldane. I am sorry that I was not well enough
                    to be there.</p>
                <p>I want to congratulate you upon getting Lord Grey’s consent to go to the United
                    States. His appointment will have a splendid influence, and add to what you have
                    already done to bring our two countries closer together.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>[File copy not signed]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
